[17:39] <lucs> Now I'd like Foo() to simply pass its args to Baz(), something like:

[17:39] <lucs> sub Foo (?) { Baz(?) }; Foo('A', :b('B'));  # Want "ABC". How?

[17:39] <lizmat> sub Foo(|c) { Baz(|c) }

